•  What you need: 
•  Java 1.5 o superior  
•  What to do: 
•  Download NOR2O  
 http://oeg-dev.dia.fi.upm.es/nor2o/#download 
•  Extract the files in your workspace folder. 
•  The current distribution comes with three examples in folders 
example1, example2 and example3. 
•  Files in the wiki 
•  “Paro” case: Unemployement for each city by date, genre and age 
•  “Atlas” case: Number of health centers for each city by year 
•  Run nor2o from the command line 
•  Wait until it finishes and check the generated RDF file
